column5: well, with some time to burn this afternoon, I headed out to the local fishin' hole with my rod and a couple jigs in my pocket.  Two hours later I was done fishing, with a couple nice walleye for dinner. I also released a OOS rainbow (about 9 pounds) and a OOS smallmouth (15 inches).  Not bad for just burning some time.
Not bad for a couple hours, think this warm spell has'em on the move...
Can somebody tell me what OOS means? Thanks...  G
Not bad at all for a couple of hours.  Please bring the camera next time we love reports with pics.  Grant OOS means OUT OF SEASON fish.MTP
Bizzare weather calls for innovative tactics.
Thanks MTP. These acronyms are a little confusing a times.
